text: Fatemeh Rahbar (; 1964 – 7 March 2020) was an Iranian politician. She served as a member of the Islamic Consultative Assembly from 2004 to 2016. She died before retaking office in 2020. Rahbar was born in Tehran. On 7 March 2020, Rahbar died in Tehran due to COVID-19 during the 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic. She was 56. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Politicians from Tehran Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Tehran Category:Elected officials who died without taking their seats
